---
description: Use openapi-extract to create small OpenAPI specs for AI coding tasks
globs: "**/*"
alwaysApply: false
---

When a task needs OpenAPI context, do not load a large OpenAPI file directly if `openapi-extract` can be used.

Install the CLI if needed:

```bash
go install github.com/korECM/openapi-extract@latest
```

Preferred flow:

```bash
openapi-extract list <openapi.yaml|url|-> --format json
openapi-extract extract <openapi.yaml|url|-> --id '<operation-id>' --stdout
```

If the CLI is not installed but the current workspace is the `openapi-extract` repository, use `go run .`:

```bash
go run . list <openapi.yaml|-> --format json
go run . extract <openapi.yaml|-> --id '<operation-id>' --stdout
```

Use `--stdout` for agent workflows, `--copy` for interactive user workflows, and `--output <file>` when the user asks for a saved mini spec.
